THE elimination of Chile from the Copa America at the hands of Brazil left Arturo Vidal hot under the collar. The Inter Milan midfielder could not hide his disgust at Argentine referee Patrico Loustau, who he blasted for unfair officiating. “Sad for the result, I think we deserve much more. I said it before, in this game you need a referee who has the pants, a referee who is fair and does not want to be the clown of the game,” said Vidal after the game. “We missed the goal, we failed to define. If there is a referee who does not let you play, who stops you everything, who believes the owner of the show is very difficult. 